REFRESHED AND RE-IMAGINE!!  Located on a quiet, tree-lined street in the heart of Sag Harbor Village, this contemporary 4 bedroom, 4 ½ bathroom residence, has an airy floor plan of 3,638 sf+/- with an elevator.  A charming entry porch leads to the main level, offering an eat-in kitchen, an open-concept living/dining area with a fireplace, a powder room, and a terrace which overlooks the pool and courtyard. The lower level in-law or grad suite has its own kitchen, a living room, a bedroom, a full bathroom, and its own garden terrace. The second level, where three exposures deliver gorgeous light into the two guest rooms has a master suite with fireplace and bathroom with shower, bathtub, and 3 closets. The third-level office suite has an en-suite bathroom and a harbor-facing terrace with an outdoor shower. The home includes an attached two-car garage (#85) with private storage (377 sf+/-). The townhouse at Watchcase are inspired by the turn-of-the-century sea captain's homes, beach-side bungalows, and cottages that populated the village. This residence represents the best of both worlds: enjoying extensive conveniences and amenities at Watchcase while maintaining the privacy and space of a single-family residence. Watchcase is perfectly positioned just one block from Sag Harbor's quaint Main Street, and two blocks from the Hamptons' only deep-water port. Watchcase encompasses 64 residences, including factory lofts and penthouses, townhouses, and bungalow condominiums. Owners benefit from elite services and hotel-style amenities, including five-star concierge services, a saltwater pool, The Watchcase Pavilion (a holistic fitness center & events lounge), The Grand Lobby Living Room, and The Vault Bar, which features a commanding two-sided fireplace. 14 Sage Street represents a rare and singular opportunity to enjoy the best of this ultra-modern community.  CAM charges $3,324.

remarks.remark: Nestled in the foothills of towering Mount Tamalpais, Mill Valley is an intimate community whose beauty is only matched by its rich Marin County history. Mill Valley is home to municipally maintained open-space reserves, parks, and coastal habitats. These areas, along with the Mediterranean climate, allow the residents to enjoy outdoor recreation year round. Wrapping around Lytton Square, the business district offers art galleries, trendy fashion boutiques, open-air coffee shops, and more. Located on 4.8 square miles, Mill Valley lies between Mt. Tamalpais on the west, the city of Tiburon on the east, the City of Corte Madera on the north and the Golden Gate National Recreational Area (GGNRA) on the south. There are two beautiful streams that flow from the slopes of Mt. Tamalpais through Mill Valley to the San Francisco Bay, the Arroyo Corte Madera del Presidio and Cascade Creek. The environmental advocacy on the part of the residents ensures that the nature enveloping the city will thrive for future generations. Mill Valley accommodates a population of about 14,000 residents.

remarks.remark: 781 Lake Avenue

Enjoy resort living at home! Exceptional Mid-Country estate encompasses over five private acres of spectacular gardens, specimen trees and sweeping lawns. Minutes to town, schools and train, the sun-filled, pre-war residence has been completely and masterfully renovated to the highest standards under the expert guidance of noted architect Laurent DuPont. Characterized by beautifully proportioned rooms, high ceilings, magnificent architectural detail and extraordinary craftsmanship, this remarkable home offers amenities for a contemporary lifestyle while retaining the original ambiance and timeless elegance. Highlighted by Brazilian cherry floors, a gracious reception hall introduces nearly 11,000 sf of warmly welcoming interiors. A grand front-to-back living room features a fireplace and French doors to a large stone terrace extending across the back of the house, perfect for entertaining. An adjacent loggia has French doors to the terrace and a handsome mahogany library is accented by a beautiful plaster relief ceiling, bookcases and wet bar. The stylish dining room also offers a fireplace and French doors to the terrace. The gourmet kitchen and adjacent family room with fireplace are the heart of the home--both have access to the terrace. A true work-of-art staircase leads past a stunning double-height window to the second floor. The impressive master suite includes a large bedroom, sitting area, octagonal office, two spa-like Waterworks marble bathrooms and two dressing rooms. There are four additional bedrooms, four baths and family room with cathedral ceiling. A third floor offers a home gym, yoga room, sixth bedroom and bath. The lower level offers another family room with fireplace, playroom and wine cellar. A fabulous 2300+ guest house offering a 3-room apartment and pool cabana, carriage house with 3 additional garage bays and unfinished space above, heated pool w/spa and all-weather tennis court complete this very special gated compound. Amazing value!

remarks.remark: Sea Colony Luxury Condo

One of the best priced luxury condos in a beachfront resort along the entire Santa Monica coastline. Steps to the beach, this west facing corner unit is located in the prestigious Sea Colony III luxury condo resort. This second floor unit boasts a large wrap around balcony with grassy courtyard views along with gentle sounds of the ocean. The interior is a smart design of high ceilings, wood floors, open kitchen with bar, new appliances with in-unit laundry, a formal dining area, spacious living room with fireplace, sliding glass doors that open to the expansive balcony. The large bedroom hosts a walk-in closet and bathroom with dual sinks, glass shower and separate bathtub. This condo property comes with two secure and covered parking spaces and a large external storage unit.

Conveniently situated on the second floor, this spacious one bedroom, one and a half bath condo is on the same floor as most of the resorts shared amenities. The first residence from the elevator and only steps down a scenic open air corridor that parallels a fountain waterfall and garden feature to the fitness center, sauna, community lounge with fireplace and chef’s kitchen that open to the heated pool and Jacuzzi deck. An expansive courtyard covered with beautiful green grass, two additional Jacuzzis/sun decks, along with a large ocean view deck all within the resort. This exclusive luxury resort community of 153 townhomes and condos has 24/7 security, covered guest parking, a comfortable lobby, on site property management and maintenance.

An easy scenic ocean view walk leads to tennis courts, basketball courts, a grassy beachfront park, children’s playground, Perry’s Café on the beach and the iconic Venice/Santa Monica boardwalk with a short stroll to the world famous Santa Monica Pier. One block away is Santa Monica’s charming main street full of boutique shopping and cafes. This destination luxury resort property has the best of SoCal beachfront lifestyle and culture.

GORGEOUS CUSTOM CRAFTSMAN HOME This gorgeous custom craftsman influenced home was designed by award winning Studio Z architects and constructed by acclaimed Sandy Spring Builders. From the stunning gourmet kitchen with expansive center island, to the adjoining family room with coffered ceiling, twosided fieldstone fireplace and custom built in cabinetry/display shelving, to the sun-filled library/sunroom, no detail has been compromised in presenting this home of distinction. A fabulous master bedroom with vaulted ceilings adorns the upper level while private screened porch affords almost full season entertaining and relaxation. A fully finished walk out lower level is complete with enormous recreation room/game room, exercise room and guest suite while a terrific deck overlooks a serene, level and private backyard. remarks.remark:
Napa is the largest of Napa Valley's towns, and is conveniently located just an hour north of San Francisco and southwest of Sacramento. You might get the impression that Napa has always been awash with vineyards and tourists clambering for a taste of the best wines in the world, but the first business establishment in the city of Napa was once a saloon. Today, with its selection of single family homes, farm homes, and vineyards, the city of Napa is synonymous with quality and diversity, and gives you access to one of the most beautiful wine regions in the world.
The city of Napa is a truly special place. Those lucky enough to find the perfect home for sale in Napa will be moving to a place surrounded by breathtaking views of rolling hills, one of the best climates in the world, and some of Northern California's best-preserved historic neighborhoods.
The city of Napa sits at the southern end of the Napa Valley. Once just a spring board for Wine Country excursions, this lovely town has become a world-class destination for more than just wine. Between amazing meals and wine tastings, there are endless other things to do in Napa, CA.
A great location for those who commute or need to conveniently travel to other ends of the state, with easy highways connecting to the East Bay, Fairfield, and Sonoma and Marin counties, Napa is also served by airports in neighboring Sonoma County, Oakland, and Sacramento.

remarks.remark: Best Development opportunity on the flats of Broad Beach. With approximately 50 feet of beach frontage, 16,800 + Sq. Ft. lot, this property has tremendous estate potential. Broad Beach remains highly desirable and one of the deepest and sandy beaches in all of Malibu. The existing Spanish style hideaway is a great second home or enjoyable beach get-away while you conceptualize and design its transformation. For the car enthusiast this home provides eight off street parking spaces including a four-car garage. At this price, this may be the best investment opportunity on the beach in Malibu today.
Malibu's Sought-After Broad Beach Road
Provence Meets The Hamptons

A frequent judge on Iron Chef, the owner of this home designed it with entertaining in mind. Not only is there a large eat-in kitchen, but there is also a large outdoor kitchen with professional pizza oven. Inspired by Provençal villas in the south of France, it magically merges the Mediterranean with the Hamptons. Set high on a hill, it features a French country kitchen that opens to a spacious front terrace with a large stone table for outdoor dining. The outdoor kitchen and outdoor living room face a stunning free-form pool. Relax and unwind here, or meditate by the fish pond, sip rose under the pergola, or play on the bocci court. On the lower level of the house you will discover a serene yoga studio, a bedroom with its own living room and kitchen, and tons of storage. Your Hamptons haven awaits.

remarks.remark: 48 Sound Beach Avenue

Live abundantly in OG
Nestled on a convenient street close to the center of Old Greenwich, is a colonial built in 2018 by Village Square Properties, with enviable proximity to enjoy life to its fullest. The welcoming foyer with hardwood floors and powder room introduces you to spacious rooms with rich custom millwork and 10 ft. ceilings. The cozy library features built-ins. The formal dining room is conveniently located next to the state of the art gorgeous white kitchen: center-island with white quartz counter tops, Thermador stainless steel 5 burner cooktop, ovens and dishwasher. There is a full-size Electrolux stainless steel refrigerator and freezer. The walk-in pantry is a chef’s dream. The adjacent two-story family room with wood burning fireplace is a light-filled central space for gatherings. French doors lead to the stone terrace with retractable awning. The mudroom with built-ins and laundry room is located off the kitchen, with two sets of full sized washer/dryer. The two-car garage complete the level.
The second-floor master suite is a luxurious retreat. The walk-in closet in addition to double closet assures plenty of space. The white marble bath with separate whirlpool tub and shower allows for pampered relaxation. 3 bedrooms and 2 white marble baths complete the level.
The lower level is flexible space. The media room with built-ins is perfect to watch your favorite movies or sporting events. The large bedroom and full bath is ready to accommodate your guests. Two additional rooms, one with built-ins for exercise, office or play space.
Systems are top notch, including a Smart hot water heater, Prestige furnace, and a hot water circulator. The house is generator ready; a gas hookup on the terrace. There are 4 heating/AC zones. 
This property is in one of the best places to live in the country with nationally ranked schools, superb convenient to fine shops, restaurants and NY City airports.
